text: the new era for Turkish politics this
may look like a celebration but it's
anything but for the first time in 13
years the ruling AKP has lost its
parliamentary majority in Ankara the
country's Prime Minister sent a message
to the other political parties
celebrating the election result the AKP
is the winner and finished first in this
election there's no doubt about that
nobody should make a victory out of an
election loss everyone should reassess
themselves the big surprise in this
election came for the pro-kurdish HDP
party which managed to attract leftist
voters with its messages on gender
equality gay rights and environmental
concerns it stormed into Parliament for
the first time winning more than 200
percent of the vote discussions about
dictatorship discussions about the
presidential system have come to an end
and Turkey as of now Turkey has been
able to step away from the brink of a
disaster the AKP party will now have to
seek a coalition partner or try and form
a shaky minority government several
parties have already ruled out joining
forces with them including the main
opposition with 25% of the vote the
Republican People's Party leader called
the results a victory for democracy a
victory for Turkey
president hurdle one hope to secure a
